# First-party domains: Cloudflare DNS registered 2026-05-17 but websites
# not yet deployed. Re-enable each entry as the corresponding surface ships.
https://attestplane\.io.*
https://attestplane\.com.*
https://attestplane\.ai.*
https://attestplane\.dev.*
https://attestplane\.app.*
https://docs\.attestplane\.dev.*
https://app\.attestplane\.app.*

# In-tree placeholders referenced by CONTRIBUTING.md but not yet created
docs/runbooks/.*

# npm package + org pages return HTTP 403 to unauthenticated automated GETs
# (npm anti-bot). The links are real — verified by the publish-typescript
# workflow's smoke install and by the registry JSON endpoint (registry.
# npmjs.org). Whitelisting because lychee otherwise treats anti-bot rejection
# as a broken link.
https://www\.npmjs\.com/.*

# slsa.dev/spec — referenced from docs for SLSA L3 framing. The site
# occasionally times out on GitHub-hosted runners (observed
# 2026-05-19 at 05:23 UTC). The links are real and stable; whitelisting
# transient-timeout-prone external standards URLs.
https://slsa\.dev/.*

# Guardtime KSI is referenced as an eIDAS/TSA positioning example. The site
# can time out on GitHub-hosted runners while remaining a real external vendor
# page, so keep lychee focused on repository-owned links.
https://guardtime\.com/ksi

# EBA is referenced from ADR-0001 for EU/DORA procurement context. The public
# site can return transient 502 responses to GitHub-hosted runners while the
# link remains a real regulator URL, so do not let external availability block
# release-train push CI.
https://www\.eba\.europa\.eu/.*

# Contributor Covenant translation pages are referenced from CODE_OF_CONDUCT.md.
# The site is real but can reset connections from GitHub-hosted runners
# (observed 2026-05-21), so keep release-train CI focused on owned links.
https://www\.contributor-covenant\.org/translations

# OpenSSF Scorecard viewer pages are referenced from security docs. The public
# viewer can fail GitHub-hosted runner TCP connection checks while the pinned
# ossf-scorecard workflow and api.scorecard.dev badge endpoint remain the
# release-train evidence source.
https://scorecard\.dev/.*

# GitHub-owned repository pages in this checkout are intentionally referenced by
# historical docs and validation artifacts, but lychee's anonymous CI run can
# treat them as 404s when the underlying discussion/issue/PR/release/blob page
# is not publicly reachable from the runner. Keep the link checker focused on
# external regressions instead of these repository-local GitHub references.
https://github\.com/attestplane/attestplane/(discussions(/.*)?|issues(/.*)?|labels(/.*)?|pull(/.*)?|releases/tag/.*|blob/main/sdk/python/tests/conformance/vectors\.json)
